.com|accessdate=6 April 2010|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|title =A biographical dictionary of civil engineers in Great Britain and Ireland| volume = 1: 1500\u20131830|isbn=072772939X|first= Alec W.|last= Skempton |first2 = R.W. |last2 = Rennison |first3 =  R.C.|last3 =  Cox |first4 =  Ted|last4= Ruddock |first5=  P.|last5= Cross-Rudkin |first6= M.M.|last6= Chrimes |publisher =  Thomas Telford Publishing Limited, Institute of Civil Engineers|year= 2002|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|title = Humberside in the Eighties|year = 1987| editor-first = David| editor-last = Symes|isbn = 0859581195|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite magazine| magazine = The Engineer| title = The Hull Joint Dock| date =30 January 1914 | volume = 117| url =http://www.gracesguide.co.uk/images/a/a8/Er19140130.pdf |ref ={{harvid|The Engineer|30 January 1914}} |at = pp. 123\u201324; ''illus.'' p. 122}}\n*{{cite magazine| magazine = The Engineer| title = The Hull Joint Dock, No. 1| date = 19 June 1914| volume = 117| url = http://www.gracesguide.co.uk/images/e/ef/Er19140619.pdf |ref ={{harvid|The Engineer|19 June 1914}} | at = pp. 674\u201376; ''illus.'' pp. 675, 678}}\n*{{cite magazine| magazine = The Engineer| title = The Hull Joint Dock, No. 2 | date = 26 June 1914| volume = 117| url = http://www.gracesguide.co.uk/images/c/cd/Er19140626.pdf|ref ={{harvid|The Engineer|26 June 1914}} |at = pp. 701\u2013704}}\n*{{cite book| title = Hull Docklands: An Illustrated History of the Port of Hull|first=Michael|last =  Thompson| publisher = Hutton Press |year =1990| isbn = 1-872167-08-X|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book| title = North Eastern Railway, Its Rise and Development| authorlink =William Weaver Tomlinson| first = William Weaver| last = Tomlinson| publisher= David & Charles|chapter = XX: Twenty-Five Years of Progress (1880\u20131904); \"Developments at Hull\"| pages = [https://archive.org/details/northeasternrail00tomlrich/page/703 703]\u2013721| url = https://archive.org/details/northeasternrail00tomlrich |year = 1914|chapterurl = ht